[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, everyone. How do you test rust modules you've written? Is there a recommended testing tool to verify module availability or bugs? In particular, how to verify that rust modules you write don't have bugs.</p>",
        "id": 440707862,
        "sender_full_name": "wenzhao",
        "timestamp": 1716724053
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/arighi/virtme-ng\">https://github.com/arighi/virtme-ng</a></p>",
        "id": 464273295,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1724308094
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is also KUnit. Rust doctests are converted to kunit if you enable kunit. You can then run the tests in qemu with the kunit make target.</p>",
        "id": 464275221,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1724308823
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is a patch for #[test] somewhere as well</p>",
        "id": 464275314,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1724308857
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In this link <a href=\"https://docs.kernel.org/rust/testing.html\">https://docs.kernel.org/rust/testing.html</a>  there is documentation about Kunit</p>",
        "id": 474581050,
        "sender_full_name": "Dooraim",
        "timestamp": 1727959099
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291567-Modules/topic/How.20to.20test.20your.20rust.20module/near/464275314\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There is a patch for #[test] somewhere as well</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>How would you search for this?</p>",
        "id": 475697582,
        "sender_full_name": "Tamir Duberstein",
        "timestamp": 1728433184
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"761630\">Tamir Duberstein</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291567-Modules/topic/How.20to.20test.20your.20rust.20module/near/475697582\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291567-Modules/topic/How.20to.20test.20your.20rust.20module/near/464275314\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There is a patch for #[test] somewhere as well</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>How would you search for this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I would go to rust-for-linux on lore and use the query \"s:kunit and s:macro\". That finds <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20230720-rustbind-v1-1-c80db349e3b5@google.com/#r\">this thread</a>, which is probably what you want.</p>",
        "id": 475822407,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1728470126
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>They use <code>#[kunit_tests]</code> rather than <code>#[test]</code></p>",
